<article>
    <h1>ArtScience On Screen: Ode To In&#xAD;ven&#xAD;tion</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200828/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-28"><time>2020-08-28</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>This short film pro­gramme com­prises four in­ter­na­tional works fea­tur­ing young in­ven­tors and their creations. Among the of­fer­ings is the French film Icare (2017, PG), in which an in­ven­tor liv­ing on a tiny is­land dreams of fly­ing with his arms and finds the per­fect can­di­date in 11-year-old Joseph. The pro­gramme is pre­sented in part­ner­ship with Imag­ine Science Films, a non-profit that pro­motes high-level di­a­logue be­tween sci­en­tists and film-mak­ers; and Labocine, Imag­ine’s ini­tia­tive which ex­tends film pro­gram­ming to a broader and more di­verse au­di­ence.</p>
    <p>ArtScience Mu­seum, The Shoppes at Ma­rina Bay Sands, 6 Bayfront Av­enue Bayfront</p>
    <p>Till Sept 11. Hourly screen­ings from 10am to 6pm (last screen­ing)</p>
    <p>Free on a first-come­first-served ba­sis, limited to 10 peo­ple a screen­ing.</p>


